{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a6df6e22-c2ea-4498-a4e8-e1120778e6f8","content":"Yes, you'll hit compatibility issues. Here's the breakdown:\n\n**Framework Support Dropped in MSTest v3:**\n- **`netcoreapp3.1`** — not supported (EOL). Upgrade to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net5.0`** — not supported (EOL). Upgrade to `net6.0` or later.\n- **`net462`** — still supported ✅\n\n**Package Changes:**\nMSTest v3 consolidates `MSTest.TestFramework` + `MSTest.TestAdapter` into a single **`MSTest`** meta-package. You can replace both references with:\n```xml\n<PackageReference Include=\"MSTest\" Version=\"3.x.x\" />\n```\n\n**To migrate**, you'd need to:\n1. Update `TargetFrameworks` to replace `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` with supported versions (e.g., `net6.0`, `net8.0`).\n2. Replace the two MSTest package references with the unified `MSTest` package.\n3. Review any behavioral/API breaking changes in MSTest v3 (e.g., stricter test lifecycle, changes to `DataRow` handling).\n\nWould you like me to update the `.csproj` for you?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"a796481b-3a44-4675-b7f5-aa3df4e21e00","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user's project targets `net5.0`, `net462`, and `netcoreapp3.1`. They want to migrate from MSTest v2 (2.2.10) to MSTest v3.\n\nMSTest v3 has some important compatibility changes:\n\n1. **Framework support**: MSTest v3 dropped support for older frameworks. Specifically:\n   - `.NET 5.0` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `netcoreapp3.1` is no longer supported (it's end-of-life)\n   - `.NET Framework 4.6.2` (`net462`) — MSTest v3 requires .NET Framework 4.6.2 or later, so `net462` should still be supported.\n   - MSTest v3 requires .NET 6.0 or later for .NET Core projects, and supports .NET Standard 2.0.\n\n2. **Package consolidation**: MSTest v3 merges the separate `MSTest.TestFramework` and `MSTest.TestAdapter` packages into a single `MSTest` package, though the legacy packages may still function.\n\n3. **Breaking changes**: There are various API and behavioral changes to be aware of.\n\nThe key takeaway is that `net5.0` and `netcoreapp3.1` targets won't work with MSTest v3 and need to be upgraded to `net6.0` or later, while `net462` remains supported.","outputTokens":754,"requestId":"0423:13264:60D2E4:7164E7:69E831B4"},"id":"226c327e-3cc5-4719-8b57-27c91e54fa39","timestamp":"2026-04-22T02:26:10.428Z","parentId":"ae887658-e6c1-4ae3-b9f0-2fc381bc35d2"}
